<subSubSection pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,151,824]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,692,717]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos, 2002" authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2002" box="[697,976,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divisus">
<emphasis box="[697,812,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">A. divisus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[825,976,692,716]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" refId="ref281712" refString="Santos, H. S. (2002) Species of Anisepyris Kieffer, 1905 (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae) collected in Cachoeira da Fumaca and Forno Grande Parks, Espirito Santo, Brazil. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 46, 243 - 249. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262002000300003" type="journal article">Santos, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
only by having the genitalia with the paramere with its dorsal arm short and wide, and its ventral arm short with its apex rounded, and the aedeagus with the basal portion distinctly angulate, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2002" box="[666,775,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divisus">
<emphasis box="[666,775,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">A. divisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the genitalia with paramere ventral arm with its apical margin truncate and its dorsal arm rounded, and the aedeagus with the basal portion convex and slender.
</paragraph>
